{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861784081,"sessionID":"ses_286640c0dffe2rD36uP62Wo9IW","part":{"id":"prt_d799c478d001Bd6VnV7JoXZEVd","messageID":"msg_d799c3173001QTDlpMaVBqNBQp","sessionID":"ses_286640c0dffe2rD36uP62Wo9IW","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-010 — Router 会话管理 (Router Session Management)\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Implement session management functionality in `pkg/router` to handle the complete lifecycle of sessions between clients and sandbox instances. The Session Manager serves as the bridge between incoming HTTP requests and sandbox instances, integrating with the Kubernetes API via client-go to manage AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources, maintaining session state in the session store, and ensuring proper session affinity for routing.\n6: \n7: The Session Manager handles four primary responsibilities:\n8: 1. **Session Resolution**: Maps session IDs to sandbox endpoints using the session store with fallback to Kubernetes resource lookup\n9: 2. **Session Lifecycle**: Manages session creation, updates, expiration, and cleanup through the store interface\n10: 3. **Session Affinity**: Ensures consistent routing of requests to the same sandbox instance within a session\n11: 4. **Resource Integration**: Uses client-go to interact with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Scope\n16: \n17: ### In scope\n18: \n19: | Item | Detail |\n20: |------|--------|\n21: | **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router` |\n22: | **Core functionality** | Session creation, resolution, state tracking, lifecycle management, affinity routing |\n23: | **Integration with** | Session store (Redis/Valkey), Kubernetes API via client-go (AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter), Workload Manager |\n24: | **Protocols** | HTTP session headers (`x-agentcube-session-id`), WebSocket session tracking |\n25: | **CRD Types** | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1.AgentRuntime`, `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter` |\n26: | **Configuration** | Session timeouts, TTL defaults, cleanup intervals via config |\n27: | **Observability** | Session metrics (active sessions, creation rate, expiration), structured logging |\n28: \n29: ### Out of scope\n30: \n31: - HTTP reverse proxy implementation (handled by AR-009)\n32: - JWT signing and authentication (handled by AR-009)\n33: - TLS termination (handled by AR-009)\n34: - Direct sandbox pod management (handled by Workload Manager)\n35: - Multi-cluster session replication (single cluster scope)\n36: - Session state persistence beyond store TTL (ephemeral session model)\n37: \n38: ---\n39: \n40: ## Design\n41: \n42: ### File layout\n43: \n44: | File | Role |\n45: |------|------|\n46: | `pkg/router/session_manager.go` | **NEW** — SessionManager interface and core implementation |\n47: | `pkg/router/session_store.go` | **NEW** — Store-backed session persistence layer |\n48: | `pkg/router/session_resolver.go` | **NEW** — Session-to-sandbox resolution logic |\n49: | `pkg/router/session_lifecycle.go` | **NEW** — Session creation, expiration, cleanup handlers |\n50: | `pkg/router/session_affinity.go` | **NEW** — Session affinity and sticky routing logic |\n51: | `pkg/router/k8s_client.go` | **NEW** — Kubernetes client-go wrapper for CRD operations |\n52: | `pkg/router/session_metrics.go` | **NEW** — Session-related Prometheus metrics |\n53: | `pkg/router/session_types.go` | **NEW** — Session-specific type definitions |\n54: \n55: ### Type definitions\n56: \n57: **`SessionManager`** — Main session management interface:\n58: \n59: ```go\n60: // SessionManager handles the complete lifecycle of sessions.\n61: type SessionManager interface {\n62:     // Resolve resolves a session ID to sandbox information.\n63:     // Creates a new session if not found and createIfMissing is true.\n64:     Resolve(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, runtimeRef RuntimeReference, createIfMissing bool) (*SessionInfo, error)\n65:     \n66:     // Create creates a new session for the given runtime.\n67:     Create(ctx context.Context, runtimeRef RuntimeReference) (*SessionInfo, error)\n68:     \n69:     // Refresh updates session activity timestamp and extends TTL.\n70:     Refresh(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n71:     \n72:     // Terminate ends a session and triggers sandbox cleanup.\n73:     Terminate(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n74:     \n75:     // Get retrieves session information by ID.\n76:     Get(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*SessionInfo, error)\n77:     \n78:     // ListActive returns all active sessions with optional filtering.\n79:     ListActive(ctx context.Context, filter SessionFilter) ([]*SessionInfo, error)\n80: }\n81: \n82: // RuntimeReference identifies a runtime resource.\n83: type RuntimeReference struct {\n84:     Kind      string // \"AgentRuntime\" or \"CodeInterpreter\"\n85:     Name      string\n86:     Namespace string\n87: }\n88: ```\n89: \n90: **`SessionInfo`** — Session metadata:\n91: \n92: ```go\n93: // SessionInfo contains all information about an active session.\n94: type SessionInfo struct {\n95:     // SessionID is the unique session identifier (UUID v4)\n96:     SessionID string `json:\"sessionId\"`\n97:     \n98:     // SandboxID links to the sandbox instance\n99:     SandboxID string `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n100:     \n101:     // RuntimeRef identifies the source runtime resource\n102:     RuntimeRef RuntimeReference `json:\"runtimeRef\"`\n103:     \n104:     // Status is the current session status\n105:     Status SessionStatus `json:\"status\"`\n106:     \n107:     // CreatedAt is when the session was created\n108:     CreatedAt time.Time `json:\"createdAt\"`\n109:     \n110:     // LastActivity is when the session was last accessed\n111:     LastActivity time.Time `json:\"lastActivity\"`\n112:     \n113:     // ExpiresAt is when the session will expire\n114:     ExpiresAt time.Time `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n115:     \n116:     // EntryPoints cache for routing (copied from SandboxInfo)\n117:     EntryPoints []types.SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n118: }\n119: \n120: // SessionStatus represents the state of a session.\n121: type SessionStatus string\n122: \n123: const (\n124:     SessionStatusPending    SessionStatus = \"Pending\"\n125:     SessionStatusActive     SessionStatus = \"Active\"\n126:     SessionStatusExpiring   SessionStatus = \"Expiring\"\n127:     SessionStatusTerminated SessionStatus = \"Terminated\"\n128: )\n129: ```\n130: \n131: **`sessionManager`** — Implementation struct:\n132: \n133: ```go\n134: // sessionManager implements SessionManager.\n135: type sessionManager struct {\n136:     // store provides session persistence\n137:     store store.Store\n138:     \n139:     // k8sClient provides access to AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter CRDs\n140:     k8sClient kubernetes.Interface\n141:     \n142:     // workloadMgrAddr is the Workload Manager endpoint for sandbox creation\n143:     workloadMgrAddr string\n144:     \n145:     // httpClient for Workload Manager communication\n146:     httpClient *http.Client\n147:     \n148:     // config holds session management configuration\n149:     config *SessionConfig\n150:     \n151:     // metrics for session operations\n152:     metrics *sessionMetrics\n153: }\n154: \n155: // SessionConfig holds session management configuration.\n156: type SessionConfig struct {\n157:     // DefaultTTL is the default session time-to-live (default: 30m)\n158:     DefaultTTL time.Duration\n159:     \n160:     // MaxTTL is the maximum allowed session TTL (default: 24h)\n161:     MaxTTL time.Duration\n162:     \n163:     // CleanupInterval is how often to run expired session cleanup (default: 5m)\n164:     CleanupInterval time.Duration\n165:     \n166:     // ActivityTimeout is the duration after which an inactive session expires (default: 30m)\n167:     ActivityTimeout time.Duration\n168: }\n169: ```\n170: \n171: **`K8sClient`** — Kubernetes client wrapper:\n172: \n173: ```go\n174: // RuntimeClient provides typed access to runtime CRDs.\n175: type RuntimeClient struct {\n176:     client    runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n177:     informers externalversions.SharedInformerFactory\n178: }\n179: \n180: // GetAgentRuntime retrieves an AgentRuntime resource by namespace/name.\n181: func (c *RuntimeClient) GetAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n182: \n183: // GetCodeInterpreter retrieves a CodeInterpreter resource by namespace/name.\n184: func (c *RuntimeClient) GetCodeInterpreter(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n185: \n186: // WatchAgentRuntimes returns a watch interface for AgentRuntime changes.\n187: func (c *RuntimeClient) WatchAgentRuntimes(ctx context.Context, namespace string) (watch.Interface, error)\n188: ```\n189: \n190: ### Session Resolution Flow\n191: \n192: ```\n193: Incoming Request\n194:    │\n195:    ├──▶ Extract x-agentcube-session-id header\n196:    │\n197:    ▼\n198: SessionManager.Resolve\n199:    │\n200:    ├──▶ sessionID empty? ──Yes──▶ Create new session ──┐\n201:    │         │                                          │\n202:    │         No                                         │\n203:    │         │                                          │\n204:    │         ▼                                          │\n205:    │    Query session store by ID                       │\n206:    │         │                                          │\n207:    ├──▶ Found? ──Yes──▶ Update activity ──▶ Return info │\n208:    │         │                                          │\n209:    │         No                                         │\n210:    │         │                                          │\n211:    │         ▼                                          │\n212:    │    Check K8s resource exists?                      │\n213:    │         │                                          │\n214:    ├──▶ Exists? ──Yes──▶ Create new session ────────────┤\n215:    │         │                                          │\n216:    │         No                                         │\n217:    │         │                                          │\n218:    │         ▼                                          │\n219:    │    Return error (resource not found)               │\n220:    │                                                    │\n221:    └──▶ Session Creation ◀──────────────────────────────┘\n222:             │\n223:             ├──▶ Call Workload Manager /v1/{kind}\n224:             ├──▶ Wait for sandbox ready\n225:             ├──▶ Store session in store\n226:             └──▶ Return SessionInfo\n227: ```\n228: \n229: ### Session Creation\n230: \n231: ```go\n232: // Create creates a new session by invoking the Workload Manager.\n233: func (m *sessionManager) Create(ctx context.Context, runtimeRef RuntimeReference) (*SessionInfo, error) {\n234:     // Generate new session ID\n235:     sessionID := uuid.New().String()\n236:     \n237:     // Build Workload Manager request\n238:     endpoint := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/v1/%s\", m.workloadMgrAddr, mapKindToEndpoint(runtimeRef.Kind))\n239:     reqBody := types.CreateSandboxRequest{\n240:         Kind:      runtimeRef.Kind,\n241:         Name:      runtimeRef.Name,\n242:         Namespace: runtimeRef.Namespace,\n243:     }\n244:     \n245:     // Call Workload Manager\n246:     resp, err := m.callWorkloadManager(ctx, endpoint, reqBody)\n247:     if err != nil {\n248:         m.metrics.sessionCreations.WithLabelValues(runtimeRef.Kind, \"failed\").Inc()\n249:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create sandbox: %w\", err)\n250:     }\n251:     \n252:     // Build session info\n253:     now := time.Now()\n254:     sessionInfo := &SessionInfo{\n255:         SessionID:    sessionID,\n256:         SandboxID:    resp.SandboxID,\n257:         RuntimeRef:   runtimeRef,\n258:         Status:       SessionStatusActive,\n259:         CreatedAt:    now,\n260:         LastActivity: now,\n261:         ExpiresAt:    now.Add(m.config.DefaultTTL),\n262:         EntryPoints:  resp.EntryPoints,\n263:     }\n264:     \n265:     // Persist to store\n266:     sandboxInfo := &types.SandboxInfo{\n267:         Kind:             runtimeRef.Kind,\n268:         SandboxID:        resp.SandboxID,\n269:         SandboxNamespace: runtimeRef.Namespace,\n270:         Name:             runtimeRef.Name,\n271:         EntryPoints:      resp.EntryPoints,\n272:         SessionID:        sessionID,\n273:         CreatedAt:        now,\n274:         ExpiresAt:        sessionInfo.ExpiresAt,\n275:         Status:           resp.Status,\n276:     }\n277:     \n278:     if err := m.store.StoreSandbox(ctx, sandboxInfo); err != nil {\n279:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to store session: %w\", err)\n280:     }\n281:     \n282:     m.metrics.sessionCreations.WithLabelValues(runtimeRef.Kind, \"success\").Inc()\n283:     m.metrics.activeSessions.Inc()\n284:     \n285:     return sessionInfo, nil\n286: }\n287: ```\n288: \n289: ### Session Affinity\n290: \n291: ```go\n292: // AffinityRouter provides sticky session routing.\n293: type AffinityRouter struct {\n294:     // sessionIndex maps session IDs to sandbox endpoints\n295:     sessionIndex map[string]*EndpointEntry\n296:     \n297:     // mu protects sessionIndex\n298:     mu sync.RWMutex\n299: }\n300: \n301: // EndpointEntry represents a routable endpoint for a session.\n302: type EndpointEntry struct {\n303:     SessionID   string\n304:     SandboxID   string\n305:     Endpoint    string\n306:     LastUsed    time.Time\n307: }\n308: \n309: // GetEndpoint returns the endpoint for a session, updating last used time.\n310: func (r *AffinityRouter) GetEndpoint(sessionID string) (*EndpointEntry, bool) {\n311:     r.mu.RLock()\n312:     defer r.mu.RUnlock()\n313:     \n314:     entry, ok := r.sessionIndex[sessionID]\n315:     if !ok {\n316:         return nil, false\n317:     }\n318:     \n319:     // Update last used time (using copy-on-write pattern)\n320:     entry.LastUsed = time.Now()\n321:     return entry, true\n322: }\n323: \n324: // RegisterSession adds a new session to the affinity index.\n325: func (r *AffinityRouter) RegisterSession(sessionInfo *SessionInfo) {\n326:     r.mu.Lock()\n327:     defer r.mu.Unlock()\n328:     \n329:     // Use first entry point as primary endpoint\n330:     if len(sessionInfo.EntryPoints) > 0 {\n331:         ep := sessionInfo.EntryPoints[0]\n332:         endpoint := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s://%s\", ep.Protocol, ep.Endpoint)\n333:         \n334:         r.sessionIndex[sessionInfo.SessionID] = &EndpointEntry{\n335:             SessionID: sessionID,\n336:             SandboxID: sessionInfo.SandboxID,\n337:             Endpoint:  endpoint,\n338:             LastUsed:  time.Now(),\n339:         }\n340:     }\n341: }\n342: ```\n343: \n344: ### Session Lifecycle Management\n345: \n346: ```go\n347: // StartLifecycleManager starts background goroutines for session maintenance.\n348: func (m *sessionManager) StartLifecycleManager(stopCh <-chan struct{}) {\n349:     // Cleanup ticker for expired sessions\n350:     cleanupTicker := time.NewTicker(m.config.CleanupInterval)\n351:     defer cleanupTicker.Stop()\n352:     \n353:     for {\n354:         select {\n355:         case <-cleanupTicker.C:\n356:             m.cleanupExpiredSessions(context.Background())\n357:         case <-stopCh:\n358:             return\n359:         }\n360:     }\n361: }\n362: \n363: // cleanupExpiredSessions removes expired sessions from the store.\n364: func (m *sessionManager) cleanupExpiredSessions(ctx context.Context) error {\n365:     expiredSandboxes, err := m.store.ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, time.Now(), 100)\n366:     if err != nil {\n367:         return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to list expired sandboxes: %w\", err)\n368:     }\n369:     \n370:     for _, sandbox := range expiredSandboxes {\n371:         // Terminate session\n372:         if err := m.Terminate(ctx, sandbox.SessionID); err != nil {\n373:             klog.Errorf(\"Failed to terminate expired session %s: %v\", sandbox.SessionID, err)\n374:             continue\n375:         }\n376:         \n377:         m.metrics.sessionsExpired.Inc()\n378:         m.metrics.activeSessions.Dec()\n379:     }\n380:     \n381:     return nil\n382: }\n383: \n384: // Refresh updates session activity and extends expiration.\n385: func (m *sessionManager) Refresh(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error {\n386:     info, err := m.store.GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n387:     if err != nil {\n388:         return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get session: %w\", err)\n389:     }\n390:     \n391:     // Update last activity\n392:     if err := m.store.UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, time.Now()); err != nil {\n393:         return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to update activity: %w\", err)\n394:     }\n395:     \n396:     // Extend expiration if needed (capped at MaxTTL from creation)\n397:     newExpiry := time.Now().Add(m.config.DefaultTTL)\n398:     maxExpiry := info.CreatedAt.Add(m.config.MaxTTL)\n399:     if newExpiry.After(maxExpiry) {\n400:         newExpiry = maxExpiry\n401:     }\n402:     \n403:     info.ExpiresAt = newExpiry\n404:     if err := m.store.UpdateSandbox(ctx, info); err != nil {\n405:         return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to update expiration: %w\", err)\n406:     }\n407:     \n408:     return nil\n409: }\n410: ```\n411: \n412: ### Kubernetes Integration via client-go\n413: \n414: ```go\n415: // NewK8sClient creates a Kubernetes client for runtime CRDs.\n416: func NewK8sClient(config *rest.Config) (*RuntimeClient, error) {\n417:     // Create clientset\n418:     clientset, err := kubernetes.NewForConfig(config)\n419:     if err != nil {\n420:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create k8s client: %w\", err)\n421:     }\n422:     \n423:     // Create runtime client (from generated client-go)\n424:     runtimeClient := runtimev1alpha1.NewForConfigOrDie(config)\n425:     \n426:     // Create informer factory\n427:     informerFactory := externalversions.NewSharedInformerFactory(clientset, 10*time.Minute)\n428:     \n429:     return &RuntimeClient{\n430:         client:    runtimeClient,\n431:         informers: informerFactory,\n432:     }, nil\n433: }\n434: \n435: // ResolveRuntime looks up runtime configuration from K8s CRDs.\n436: func (c *RuntimeClient) ResolveRuntime(ctx context.Context, ref RuntimeReference) (*RuntimeConfig, error) {\n437:     switch ref.Kind {\n438:     case \"AgentRuntime\":\n439:         ar, err := c.client.AgentRuntimes(ref.Namespace).Get(ctx, ref.Name, metav1.GetOptions{})\n440:         if err != nil {\n441:             return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get AgentRuntime: %w\", err)\n442:         }\n443:         return extractRuntimeConfig(ar)\n444:         \n445:     case \"CodeInterpreter\":\n446:         ci, err := c.client.CodeInterpreters(ref.Namespace).Get(ctx, ref.Name, metav1.GetOptions{})\n447:         if err != nil {\n448:             return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get CodeInterpreter: %w\", err)\n449:         }\n450:         return extractRuntimeConfig(ci)\n451:         \n452:     default:\n453:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unsupported runtime kind: %s\", ref.Kind)\n454:     }\n455: }\n456: ```\n457: \n458: ### Metrics\n459: \n460: ```go\n461: var (\n462:     sessionCreations = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n463:         prometheus.CounterOpts{\n464:             Name: \"agentcube_session_creations_total\",\n465:             Help: \"Total session creations by kind and result\",\n466:         },\n467:         []string{\"kind\", \"result\"},\n468:     )\n469:     \n470:     activeSessions = prometheus.NewGauge(\n471:         prometheus.GaugeOpts{\n472:             Name: \"agentcube_active_sessions\",\n473:             Help: \"Current number of active sessions\",\n474:         },\n475:     )\n476:     \n477:     sessionsExpired = prometheus.NewCounter(\n478:         prometheus.CounterOpts{\n479:             Name: \"agentcube_sessions_expired_total\",\n480:             Help: \"Total sessions expired\",\n481:         },\n482:     )\n483:     \n484:     sessionResolveDuration = prometheus.NewHistogramVec(\n485:         prometheus.HistogramOpts{\n486:             Name:    \"agentcube_session_resolve_duration_seconds\",\n487:             Help:    \"Session resolution duration\",\n488:             Buckets: prometheus.DefBuckets,\n489:         },\n490:         []string{\"cache_hit\"},\n491:     )\n492:     \n493:     sessionDuration = prometheus.NewHistogram(\n494:         prometheus.HistogramOpts{\n495:             Name:    \"agentcube_session_duration_seconds\",\n496:             Help:    \"Total session lifetime duration\",\n497:             Buckets: []float64{60, 300, 600, 1800, 3600, 7200, 86400},\n498:         },\n499:     )\n500: )\n501: ```\n502: \n503: ### Default Configuration\n504: \n505: | Parameter | Default | Description |\n506: |-----------|---------|-------------|\n507: | `DefaultTTL` | 30m | Default session time-to-live |\n508: | `MaxTTL` | 24h | Maximum allowed session TTL |\n509: | `CleanupInterval` | 5m | Expired session cleanup interval |\n510: | `ActivityTimeout` | 30m | Inactivity timeout for sessions |\n511: \n512: ### Error Handling\n513: \n514: ```go\n515: // SessionError represents session management errors.\n516: type SessionError struct {\n517:     Code    string\n518:     Message string\n519:     Cause   error\n520: }\n521: \n522: func (e *SessionError) Error() string { return e.Message }\n523: func (e *SessionError) Unwrap() error { return e.Cause }\n524: \n525: var (\n526:     ErrSessionNotFound    = &SessionError{Code: \"SESSION_NOT_FOUND\", Message: \"session not found\"}\n527:     ErrSessionExpired     = &SessionError{Code: \"SESSION_EXPIRED\", Message: \"session has expired\"}\n528:     ErrRuntimeNotFound    = &SessionError{Code: \"RUNTIME_NOT_FOUND\", Message: \"runtime resource not found\"}\n529:     ErrSandboxCreateFailed = &SessionError{Code: \"SANDBOX_CREATE_FAILED\", Message: \"failed to create sandbox\"}\n530: )\n531: ```\n532: \n533: ---\n534: \n535: ## Impact Analysis\n536: \n537: ### Files created/modified\n538: \n539: | File | Lines (est.) | Type |\n540: |------|-------------|------|\n541: | `pkg/router/session_manager.go` | ~250 | New |\n542: | `pkg/router/session_store.go` | ~150 | New |\n543: | `pkg/router/session_resolver.go` | ~180 | New |\n544: | `pkg/router/session_lifecycle.go` | ~200 | New |\n545: | `pkg/router/session_affinity.go` | ~120 | New |\n546: | `pkg/router/k8s_client.go` | ~150 | New |\n547: | `pkg/router/session_metrics.go` | ~80 | New |\n548: | `pkg/router/session_types.go` | ~100 | New |\n549: \n550: ### Downstream consumers\n551: \n552: | Consumer | Dependency |\n553: |----------|-----------|\n554: | Router (AR-009) | Uses SessionManager for session resolution |\n555: | Client SDK | Relies on session headers for affinity |\n556: | Workload Manager | Called to create sandboxes on miss |\n557: | Session Store | Persist/read session data |\n558: | Kubernetes API | Read AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter CRDs |\n559: \n560: ### Breaking change risk\n561: \n562: - **None for existing APIs**: This is new functionality building on AR-009\n563: - **Store interface**: Uses existing store.Store interface\n564: - **CRD compatibility**: Uses generated client-go for runtime/v1alpha1 types\n565: - **Session header format**: Uses existing `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n566: \n567: ---\n568: \n569: ## Alternatives Considered\n570: \n571: ### 1. Store session state directly in Kubernetes CRDs instead of external store\n572: \n573: **Approach**: Use AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter status fields to track session state.\n574: \n575: **Rejected because**: Writing session activity to CRDs on every request would create excessive etcd write load and trigger unnecessary watch events. External store (Redis/Valkey) is optimized for high-frequency session operations while CRDs are for configuration.\n576: \n577: ### 2. Implement session management as a separate microservice\n578: \n579: **Approach**: Create a dedicated Session Manager service independent of Router.\n580: \n581: **Rejected because**: Session resolution is on the critical path for every request. Adding a network hop would introduce unacceptable latency. Tight integration within Router allows in-memory caching and direct store access.\n582: \n583: ### 3. Use client-side session cookies instead of server-side session store\n584: \n585: **Approach**: Store session state in encrypted client cookies.\n586: \n587: **Rejected because**: Session state includes sandbox endpoint information that clients should not access directly. Server-side sessions provide better security, allow forced expiration, and enable centralized session management across multiple router instances.\n588: \n589: ### 4. Use StatefulSet pod names for session affinity instead of store\n590: \n591: **Approach**: Derive session affinity from Kubernetes StatefulSet ordinal naming.\n592: \n593: **Rejected because**: AgentCube sandboxes are dynamically created pods, not StatefulSet members. Session affinity must work across pod recreations and support session migration scenarios.\n594: \n595: ### 5. Use Istio/Envoy session affinity features\n596: \n597: **Approach**: Delegate session affinity to service mesh layer.\n598: \n599: **Rejected because**: Service mesh session affinity requires consistent hashing on session ID which doesn't work well with dynamic sandbox endpoints. AgentCube's session model requires application-level knowledge of sandbox lifecycle states.\n600: \n601: ---\n602: \n603: ## Dependencies\n604: \n605: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n606: |------------|---------|---------|\n607: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Local | Session store interface |\n608: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | Local | SandboxInfo and types |\n609: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Local | Generated client for runtime CRDs |\n610: | `github.com/google/uuid` | v1.x | Session ID generation |\n611: | `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.34.1 | Kubernetes API client |\n612: | `k8s.io/api` | v0.34.1 | Kubernetes API types |\n613: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | v0.34.1 | K8s API machinery |\n614: | `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | v1.x | Metrics collection |\n615: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.x | Structured logging |\n616: \n617: ---\n618: \n619: ## Verification\n620: \n621: ```bash\n622: # Unit tests\n623: make test PKG=./pkg/router/...\n624: \n625: # Integration tests\n626: go test -v ./pkg/router/... -run \"TestSessionManager\"\n627: go test -v ./pkg/router/... -run \"TestSessionLifecycle\"\n628: go test -v ./pkg/router/... -run \"TestSessionAffinity\"\n629: \n630: # Build verification\n631: go build ./pkg/router/...\n632: \n633: # Run session lifecycle tests\n634: go test -v ./pkg/router/... -run \"TestSessionExpiration\"\n635: \n636: # Verify race conditions\n637: go test -race ./pkg/router/...\n638: \n639: # Verify with fake k8s client\n640: go test -v ./pkg/router/... -run \"TestK8sClient\"\n641: ```\n642: \n643: ---\n644: \n645: ## References\n646: \n647: - [Session Routing Design](session-routing/design.md) — Router design details\n648: - [Session Routing Specification](session-routing/spec.md) — Functional requirements\n649: - [client-go library spec](deployment/client-go.md) — Generated client details\n650: - [AR-009](changes/AR-009/design.md) — Router HTTP Reverse Proxy Core\n651: - [AR-005](changes/AR-005/design.md) — Sandbox Creation Handler\n652: - [Kubernetes client-go](https://github.com/kubernetes/client-go) — Official Go client\n653: - [client-go informers](https://pkg.go.dev/k8s.io/client-go/informers) — Caching and watching resources\n654: \n655: ---\n656: \n657: *AR-010 — Module: pkg/router — Language: Go — Size: M*\n\n(End of file - total 657 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-010 — Router 会话管理 (Router Session Management)\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement session management functionality in `pkg/router` to handle the complete lifecycle of sessions between clients and sandbox instances. The Session Manager serves as the bridge between incoming HTTP requests and sandbox instances, integrating with the Kubernetes API via client-go to manage AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources, maintaining session state in the session store, and ensuring proper session affinity for routing.\n\nThe Session Manager handles four primary responsibilities:\n1. **Session Resolution**: Maps session IDs to sandbox endpoints using the session store with fallback to Kubernetes resource lookup\n2. **Session Lifecycle**: Manages session creation, updates, expiration, and cleanup through the store interface\n3. **Session Affinity**: Ensures consistent routing of requests to the same sandbox instance within a session\n4. **Resource Integration**: Uses client-go to interact with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775861784050,"end":1775861784079}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861784084,"sessionID":"ses_286640c0dffe2rD36uP62Wo9IW","part":{"id":"prt_d799c58d7001v1k2FSiTJdB0Ka","messageID":"msg_d799c3173001QTDlpMaVBqNBQp","sessionID":"ses_286640c0dffe2rD36uP62Wo9IW","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/project.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/project.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n2: \n3: > Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n4: > Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n5: \n6: ## Purpose\n7: \n8: AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\n9: It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\n10: session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n11: \n12: ## Tech Stack\n13: \n14: | Layer | Technology |\n15: |-------|-----------|\n16: | Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n17: | Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n18: | HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n19: | Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n20: | Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |\n21: | Auth | JWT RS256 (golang-jwt/v5), K8s TokenReview |\n22: | Packaging | Helm 3, multi-stage Docker, GitHub Actions CI/CD |\n23: | Docs | Docusaurus 3.x |\n24: \n25: ## Architecture\n26: \n27: ```\n28: Client / SDK / CLI\n29:   → Router (Deployment :8080)\n30:      ↔ Redis/Valkey (session store)\n31:      → WorkloadManager (Service :8080)\n32:         ↔ Redis/Valkey\n33:         → K8s API: CRDs, Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n34:   Sandbox Pods (with optional PicoD daemon)\n35:   Agentd (idle cleanup controller)\n36:   Optional: Volcano vc-agent-scheduler\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ## Conventions\n40: \n41: - Go packages under `pkg/`, binaries under `cmd/`\n42: - Python CLI at `cmd/cli/`, SDK at `sdk-python/`\n43: - JSON tags use camelCase; Go structs use PascalCase\n44: - K8s resources use `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group\n45: - Normative language: SHALL = mandatory, SHOULD = recommended, MAY = optional\n\n(End of file - total 45 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n\n> Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n> Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n\n## Purpose\n\nAgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\nIt provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\nsession-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n| Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n| HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n| Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n| Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/project.md","time":{"start":1775861784060,"end":1775861784082}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861784097,"sessionID":"ses_286640c0dffe2rD36uP62Wo9IW","part":{"id":"prt_d799c4d01001NIZZ887EM3M0xe","messageID":"msg_d799c3173001QTDlpMaVBqNBQp","sessionID":"ses_286640c0dffe2rD36uP62Wo9IW","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-011/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-011/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-011 Design: Router JWT 认证与签发\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-011  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/router`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** Medium\n9: \n10: _TBD: Design overview for JWT authentication and issuance component_\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Architecture\n15: \n16: ### High-Level Design\n17: \n18: _TBD: Architecture diagram and component overview_\n19: \n20: ### Component Interactions\n21: \n22: | Component | Purpose | Input | Output |\n23: |-----------|---------|-------|--------|\n24: | **JWTManager** | _TBD_ | _TBD_ | _TBD_ |\n25: \n26: ---\n27: \n28: ## Directory Structure\n29: \n30: ```\n31: pkg/router/\n32: ├── doc.go                      # Package documentation\n33: ├── config.go                   # Router configuration\n34: ├── server.go                   # HTTP server\n35: ├── jwt.go                      # JWT management (_TBD: implement_)\n36: └── ...\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: ## Data Structures\n42: \n43: ### Core Types\n44: \n45: _TBD: Define JWTManager interface and implementation_\n46: \n47: ---\n48: \n49: ## API Contracts\n50: \n51: _TBD: Define API methods and behaviors_\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ## Error Handling\n56: \n57: ### Error Types\n58: \n59: _TBD: Define error types and handling patterns_\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ## Testing Strategy\n64: \n65: _TBD: Unit and integration test approach_\n66: \n67: ---\n68: \n69: ## Dependencies\n70: \n71: ### Direct Dependencies\n72: \n73: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n74: |------------|---------|---------|\n75: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.x | JWT token handling |\n76: | `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.34.1 | Kubernetes Secret storage |\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: ## Configuration\n81: \n82: ### Environment Variables\n83: \n84: | Variable | Default | Description |\n85: |----------|---------|-------------|\n86: | _TBD_ | _TBD_ | _TBD_ |\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ## Metrics\n91: \n92: _TBD: Prometheus metrics definition_\n93: \n94: ---\n95: \n96: ## Implementation Details\n97: \n98: _TBD: Key implementation details_\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## References\n103: \n104: - [AR-009](changes/AR-009/design.md) — Router HTTP Reverse Proxy Core\n105: - [AR-010](changes/AR-010/design.md) — Router Session Management\n106: - [JWT Specification](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7519) — RFC 7519\n107: \n108: ---\n109: \n110: *AR-011 — Module: pkg/router — Language: Go — Size: M*\n\n(End of file - total 110 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-011 Design: Router JWT 认证与签发\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-011  \n**Module:** `pkg/router`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** Medium\n\n_TBD: Design overview for JWT authentication and issuance component_\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Design\n\n_TBD: Architecture diagram and component overview_\n\n### Component Interactions","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-011/design.md","time":{"start":1775861784054,"end":1775861784096}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861784101,"sessionID":"ses_286640c0dffe2rD36uP62Wo9IW","part":{"id":"prt_d799c530b001S4TN9XBTSjdCap","messageID":"msg_d799c3173001QTDlpMaVBqNBQp","sessionID":"ses_286640c0dffe2rD36uP62Wo9IW","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/router/jwt.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/router/jwt.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: /*\n2: Copyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n3: \n4: Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n5: you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n6: You may obtain a copy of the License at\n7: \n8:     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n9: \n10: Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n11: distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n12: WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n13: See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n14: limitations under the License.\n15: */\n16: \n17: package router\n18: \n19: import (\n20: \t\"crypto/rand\"\n21: \t\"crypto/rsa\"\n22: \t\"crypto/x509\"\n23: \t\"encoding/pem\"\n24: \t\"fmt\"\n25: \t\"os\"\n26: \t\"time\"\n27: \n28: \t\"github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5\"\n29: \tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n30: \tapierrors \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors\"\n31: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n32: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n33: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/rest\"\n34: \t\"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n35: )\n36: \n37: const (\n38: \trsaKeySize         = 2048\n39: \tjwtExpiration      = 5 * time.Minute\n40: \tidentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"\n41: \tprivateKeyDataKey  = \"private.pem\"\n42: \tpublicKeyDataKey   = \"public.pem\"\n43: )\n44: \n45: // IdentityNamespace is the namespace where the JWT identity secret is stored.\n46: // Initialized from AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE env var or defaults to \"default\".\n47: var IdentityNamespace = \"default\"\n48: \n49: func init() {\n50: \tif ns := os.Getenv(\"AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\"); ns != \"\" {\n51: \t\tIdentityNamespace = ns\n52: \t}\n53: }\n54: \n55: // JWTManager handles JWT key generation and token signing.\n56: type JWTManager struct {\n57: \tprivateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n58: \tpublicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n59: \tclientset  kubernetes.Interface\n60: }\n61: \n62: // NewJWTManager creates a new JWTManager with a generated RSA key pair.\n63: func NewJWTManager() (*JWTManager, error) {\n64: \tprivateKey, err := rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, rsaKeySize)\n65: \tif err != nil {\n66: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to generate RSA key: %w\", err)\n67: \t}\n68: \n69: \treturn &JWTManager{\n70: \t\tprivateKey: privateKey,\n71: \t\tpublicKey:  &privateKey.PublicKey,\n72: \t}, nil\n73: }\n74: \n75: // GenerateToken creates a JWT with the given claims.\n76: func (m *JWTManager) GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error) {\n77: \tnow := time.Now()\n78: \n79: \t// Build base claims\n80: \ttokenClaims := jwt.MapClaims{\n81: \t\t\"exp\": now.Add(jwtExpiration).Unix(),\n82: \t\t\"iat\": now.Unix(),\n83: \t\t\"iss\": \"agentcube-router\",\n84: \t}\n85: \n86: \t// Merge custom claims\n87: \tfor k, v := range claims {\n88: \t\ttokenClaims[k] = v\n89: \t}\n90: \n91: \t// Create and sign token\n92: \ttoken := jwt.NewWithClaims(jwt.SigningMethodRS256, tokenClaims)\n93: \ttokenString, err := token.SignedString(m.privateKey)\n94: \tif err != nil {\n95: \t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"failed to sign token: %w\", err)\n96: \t}\n97: \n98: \treturn tokenString, nil\n99: }\n100: \n101: // GetPublicKeyPEM returns the public key in PEM format.\n102: func (m *JWTManager) GetPublicKeyPEM() ([]byte, error) {\n103: \tpublicKeyBytes, err := x509.MarshalPKIXPublicKey(m.publicKey)\n104: \tif err != nil {\n105: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to marshal public key: %w\", err)\n106: \t}\n107: \n108: \tpemBlock := &pem.Block{\n109: \t\tType:  \"PUBLIC KEY\",\n110: \t\tBytes: publicKeyBytes,\n111: \t}\n112: \n113: \treturn pem.EncodeToMemory(pemBlock), nil\n114: }\n115: \n116: // GetPrivateKeyPEM returns the private key in PEM format.\n117: func (m *JWTManager) GetPrivateKeyPEM() ([]byte, error) {\n118: \tprivateKeyBytes := x509.MarshalPKCS1PrivateKey(m.privateKey)\n119: \n120: \tpemBlock := &pem.Block{\n121: \t\tType:  \"RSA PRIVATE KEY\",\n122: \t\tBytes: privateKeyBytes,\n123: \t}\n124: \n125: \treturn pem.EncodeToMemory(pemBlock), nil\n126: }\n127: \n128: // TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret attempts to store the JWT keys in a Kubernetes secret\n129: // or load them if the secret already exists. Returns nil if not running in-cluster.\n130: func (m *JWTManager) TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret() error {\n131: \t// Try to get in-cluster config\n132: \tconfig, err := rest.InClusterConfig()\n133: \tif err != nil {\n134: \t\tklog.Warningf(\"Not running in Kubernetes cluster, using ephemeral JWT keys: %v\", err)\n135: \t\treturn nil\n136: \t}\n137: \n138: \t// Create clientset\n139: \tclientset, err := kubernetes.NewForConfig(config)\n140: \tif err != nil {\n141: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create Kubernetes client: %w\", err)\n142: \t}\n143: \n144: \tm.clientset = clientset\n145: \n146: \t// Get or create the secret\n147: \treturn m.createOrLoadSecret()\n148: }\n149: \n150: func (m *JWTManager) createOrLoadSecret() error {\n151: \t// Try to create the secret\n152: \tprivatePEM, err := m.GetPrivateKeyPEM()\n153: \tif err != nil {\n154: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to encode private key: %w\", err)\n155: \t}\n156: \n157: \tpublicPEM, err := m.GetPublicKeyPEM()\n158: \tif err != nil {\n159: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to encode public key: %w\", err)\n160: \t}\n161: \n162: \tsecret := &corev1.Secret{\n163: \t\tObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n164: \t\t\tName:      identitySecretName,\n165: \t\t\tNamespace: IdentityNamespace,\n166: \t\t\tLabels: map[string]string{\n167: \t\t\t\t\"app\":       \"agentcube\",\n168: \t\t\t\t\"component\": \"router\",\n169: \t\t\t},\n170: \t\t},\n171: \t\tType: corev1.SecretTypeOpaque,\n172: \t\tData: map[string][]byte{\n173: \t\t\tprivateKeyDataKey: privatePEM,\n174: \t\t\tpublicKeyDataKey:  publicPEM,\n175: \t\t},\n176: \t}\n177: \n178: \t_, err = m.clientset.CoreV1().Secrets(IdentityNamespace).Create(nil, secret, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n179: \tif err != nil {\n180: \t\tif apierrors.IsAlreadyExists(err) {\n181: \t\t\t// Secret exists, load the keys\n182: \t\t\treturn m.loadExistingSecret()\n183: \t\t}\n184: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create JWT secret: %w\", err)\n185: \t}\n186: \n187: \tklog.Infof(\"Created JWT identity secret '%s' in namespace '%s'\", identitySecretName, IdentityNamespace)\n188: \treturn nil\n189: }\n190: \n191: func (m *JWTManager) loadExistingSecret() error {\n192: \tsecret, err := m.clientset.CoreV1().Secrets(IdentityNamespace).Get(nil, identitySecretName, metav1.GetOptions{})\n193: \tif err != nil {\n194: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get existing JWT secret: %w\", err)\n195: \t}\n196: \n197: \tprivatePEM, ok := secret.Data[privateKeyDataKey]\n198: \tif !ok {\n199: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"existing JWT secret missing private key data\")\n200: \t}\n201: \n202: \treturn m.loadPrivateKeyPEM(privatePEM)\n203: }\n204: \n205: func (m *JWTManager) loadPrivateKeyPEM(pemData []byte) error {\n206: \tblock, _ := pem.Decode(pemData)\n207: \tif block == nil {\n208: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to decode PEM block\")\n209: \t}\n210: \n211: \tprivateKey, err := x509.ParsePKCS1PrivateKey(block.Bytes)\n212: \tif err != nil {\n213: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to parse private key: %w\", err)\n214: \t}\n215: \n216: \tm.privateKey = privateKey\n217: \tm.publicKey = &privateKey.PublicKey\n218: \n219: \tklog.Infof(\"Loaded existing JWT keys from secret '%s'\", identitySecretName)\n220: \treturn nil\n221: }\n\n(End of file - total 221 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"/*\nCopyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n\nLicensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\nyou may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\nYou may obtain a copy of the License at\n\n    http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n\nUnless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\ndistributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\nWITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\nSee the License for the specific language governing permissions and\nlimitations under the License.\n*/\n\npackage router\n\nimport (\n\t\"crypto/rand\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/router/jwt.go","time":{"start":1775861784058,"end":1775861784099}}}}
