{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861795912,"sessionID":"ses_286640c0dffe2rD36uP62Wo9IW","part":{"id":"prt_d799c7f0c001V8TMmQQ02yzmX0","messageID":"msg_d799c5e62001TZDjDoglNroXtW","sessionID":"ses_286640c0dffe2rD36uP62Wo9IW","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/session-routing/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/session-routing/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Session Routing — Design\n2: \n3: ## Module\n4: \n5: - Same repository: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` (see sandbox-orchestration design for `go.mod` and versions).\n6: \n7: ## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router`\n8: \n9: ### Config\n10: \n11: ```go\n12: const LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity\"\n13: \n14: type Config struct {\n15:     Port                  string\n16:     Debug                 bool\n17:     EnableTLS             bool\n18:     TLSCert               string\n19:     TLSKey                string\n20:     MaxConcurrentRequests int  // 0 = unlimited at flag level; NewServer coerces to 1000\n21: }\n22: ```\n23: \n24: ### CLI flags (`cmd/router/main.go`)\n25: \n26: | Flag | Default |\n27: |------|---------|\n28: | `-port` | `8080` |\n29: | `-enable-tls` | `false` |\n30: | `-tls-cert` | `\"\"` |\n31: | `-tls-key` | `\"\"` |\n32: | `-debug` | `false` |\n33: | `-max-concurrent-requests` | `1000` (0 means unlimited per flag help; `NewServer` still sets default 1000 when `<= 0`) |\n34: \n35: ### Server struct\n36: \n37: ```go\n38: type Server struct {\n39:     config         *Config\n40:     engine         *gin.Engine\n41:     httpServer     *http.Server\n42:     sessionManager SessionManager\n43:     storeClient    store.Store\n44:     httpTransport  *http.Transport\n45:     jwtManager     *JWTManager\n46: }\n47: ```\n48: \n49: - `httpTransport`: `IdleConnTimeout: 0`, `DisableCompression: false`.\n50: - Store: `store.Storage()` for both session manager and `storeClient`.\n51: - Gin mode: `DebugMode` if `config.Debug`, else `ReleaseMode`.\n52: \n53: ### Route table\n54: \n55: | Method | Path | Middleware | Handler |\n56: |--------|------|------------|---------|\n57: | GET | `/health/live` | none | `handleHealthLive` |\n58: | GET | `/health/ready` | none | `handleHealthReady` |\n59: | GET | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | `gin.Logger`, `gin.Recovery`, `concurrencyLimitMiddleware` | `handleAgentInvoke` |\n60: | POST | same | same | `handleAgentInvoke` |\n61: | GET | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | same | `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` |\n62: | POST | same | same | `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` |\n63: \n64: ### SessionManager interface\n65: \n66: ```go\n67: type SessionManager interface {\n68:     GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace string, name string, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n69: }\n70: ```\n71: \n72: ### manager implementation (`session_manager.go`)\n73: \n74: ```go\n75: type manager struct {\n76:     storeClient     store.Store\n77:     workloadMgrAddr string\n78:     httpClient      *http.Client\n79: }\n80: ```\n81: \n82: - `NewSessionManager(storeClient store.Store) (SessionManager, error)` reads `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` (required).\n83: - HTTP client: `Timeout: 2 * time.Minute`; transport `MaxIdleConnsPerHost: 100`, `DisableCompression: false`; `http2.ConfigureTransports` with `ReadIdleTimeout: 30s`, `PingTimeout: 15s`.\n84: - Endpoints: `AgentRuntime` → `{WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/agent-runtime`; `CodeInterpreter` → `.../v1/code-interpreter`.\n85: - Request: `Content-Type: application/json`; optional `Authorization: Bearer` from `loadWorkloadManagerAuthToken()` reading `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` (trimmed); missing file → no header (warning if non-NotExist error).\n86: \n87: ### JWT (`jwt.go`)\n88: \n89: **Constants (unexported unless noted):**\n90: \n91: | Name | Value |\n92: |------|--------|\n93: | `rsaKeySize` | `2048` |\n94: | `jwtExpiration` | `5 * time.Minute` |\n95: | `IdentitySecretName` | `\"picod-router-identity\"` |\n96: | `PrivateKeyDataKey` | `\"private.pem\"` |\n97: | `PublicKeyDataKey` | `\"public.pem\"` |\n98: \n99: ```go\n100: var IdentityNamespace = \"default\" // init: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE if set\n101: ```\n102: \n103: **JWTManager:**\n104: \n105: ```go\n106: type JWTManager struct {\n107:     privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n108:     publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n109:     clientset  kubernetes.Interface\n110: }\n111: ```\n112: \n113: - `NewJWTManager()`: `rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, rsaKeySize)`.\n114: - `GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)`:\n115:   - Base claims: `exp` = now+jwtExpiration (Unix), `iat` = now (Unix), `iss` = `\"agentcube-router\"`.\n116:   - Merges custom claims (e.g. `session_id`).\n117:   - Signing: `jwt.SigningMethodRS256`, signed with RSA private key.\n118: \n119: **Algorithm:** RS256  \n120: **Key type:** RSA 2048-bit, PKCS1 private key PEM (`RSA PRIVATE KEY`), PKIX public key PEM (`PUBLIC KEY`).\n121: \n122: **TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx):**\n123: \n124: - If `clientset == nil`, try `rest.InClusterConfig()`; on failure log warning and return nil (ephemeral keys).\n125: - Else build Secret `IdentitySecretName` in `IdentityNamespace`, type `Opaque`, labels `app=agentcube`, `component=router`, data `private.pem` + `public.pem`.\n126: - Create; on `AlreadyExists`, Get secret and `loadPrivateKeyPEM`.\n127: \n128: ### Reverse proxy\n129: \n130: - `httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy(targetURL)`; `proxy.Transport = s.httpTransport`.\n131: - Director: sets `req.URL.Path` to normalized path, clears `RawPath`, `req.Host = targetURL.Host`, forwarding headers, `Authorization` if JWT non-empty.\n132: - `ModifyResponse`: sets `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n133: - No per-request timeout wrapper (commented-out context timeout in source).\n134: \n135: ### Concurrency middleware\n136: \n137: - Buffered channel size `config.MaxConcurrentRequests`.\n138: - `select`: send to channel or `default` → 429 + abort.\n139: \n140: ### Health JSON shapes\n141: \n142: - Live: `{\"status\":\"alive\"}`.\n143: - Ready OK: `{\"status\":\"ready\"}`.\n144: - Ready fail: `{\"status\":\"not ready\",\"error\":\"session manager not available\"}`.\n145: \n146: ### Error helper (`handleGetSandboxError`)\n147: \n148: - If `apierrors.APIStatus`: use `Status().Code` if non-zero; message from status or `err.Error()`; if code is 500, replace message with `internal server error`; respond `gin.H{\"error\": message}`.\n149: - Else 500 `{\"error\":\"internal server error\"}`.\n150: \n151: ### Environment variables\n152: \n153: | Variable | Used by |\n154: |----------|---------|\n155: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Session manager (required) |\n156: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | JWT secret namespace (optional, default `default`) |\n157: \n158: ### Dependencies (direct use in router)\n159: \n160: - `github.com/gin-gonic/gin`, `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5`, `golang.org/x/net/http2`, `k8s.io/api`, `k8s.io/apimachinery`, `k8s.io/client-go`, `k8s.io/klog/v2`, `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store`, `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types`, `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/api`.\n\n(End of file - total 160 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Session Routing — Design\n\n## Module\n\n- Same repository: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` (see sandbox-orchestration design for `go.mod` and versions).\n\n## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router`\n\n### Config\n\n```go\nconst LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity\"\n\ntype Config struct {\n    Port                  string\n    Debug                 bool\n    EnableTLS             bool\n    TLSCert               string\n    TLSKey                string\n    MaxConcurrentRequests int  // 0 = unlimited at flag level; NewServer coerces to 1000","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/session-routing/design.md","time":{"start":1775861795897,"end":1775861795911}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861795915,"sessionID":"ses_286640c0dffe2rD36uP62Wo9IW","part":{"id":"prt_d799c83750017pt5hspVAleo7z","messageID":"msg_d799c5e62001TZDjDoglNroXtW","sessionID":"ses_286640c0dffe2rD36uP62Wo9IW","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/session-routing/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/session-routing/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Session Routing Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Route HTTP invocation traffic to sandboxes by session: resolve or create sessions via the workload manager, track activity in the store, reverse-proxy to pod endpoints, and sign outbound requests with JWT when targeting sandboxes.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Session resolution and creation\n9: The system SHALL read session id from request header `x-agentcube-session-id`. When the header is empty, the system SHALL POST to the workload manager to create a sandbox. When non-empty, the system SHALL load `SandboxInfo` from the store by session id.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Missing session triggers workload manager create\n12: - **GIVEN** `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is set and an invocation request has no `x-agentcube-session-id`\n13: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySession` runs for `AgentRuntimeKind`\n14: - **THEN** the client POSTs JSON `{\"kind\":\"AgentRuntime\",\"name\":...,\"namespace\":...}` to `{WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/agent-runtime`\n15: \n16: #### Scenario: Unknown session returns not found\n17: - **GIVEN** a non-empty session id not present in store\n18: - **WHEN** the store returns `ErrNotFound`\n19: - **THEN** the error maps to `NewSessionNotFoundError(sessionID)` and the HTTP handler responds using API status (typically 404)\n20: \n21: ### Requirement: Workload manager URL and auth token for creates\n22: The system SHALL require environment variable `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` at session manager construction (non-empty). When the file `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` exists and is readable, the system SHALL attach `Authorization: Bearer <trimmed contents>` to create requests.\n23: \n24: #### Scenario: Missing WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL fails startup\n25: - **GIVEN** `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is unset\n26: - **WHEN** `NewSessionManager` is called\n27: - **THEN** it returns error `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL environment variable is not set`\n28: \n29: ### Requirement: Create response validation\n30: The system SHALL accept workload manager HTTP 200 with body `CreateSandboxResponse`; SHALL reject with internal error if `sessionId` in body is empty; SHALL build in-memory `SandboxInfo` with `SandboxID`, `Name` (= `sandboxName`), `SessionID`, `EntryPoints` from the response (other fields may be zero).\n31: \n32: #### Scenario: Non-OK from workload manager\n33: - **GIVEN** workload manager returns HTTP 404\n34: - **WHEN** the session manager handles the response\n35: - **THEN** the error is `NewSandboxTemplateNotFoundError(namespace, name, kind)`\n36: \n37: ### Requirement: Reverse proxy to sandbox\n38: The system SHALL determine upstream URL from `SandboxInfo.EntryPoints` by first matching `path` prefix against the invocation path; if none match, SHALL use the first entry point. The system SHALL build URL by prefixing `protocol` (lowercase) and `://` to `endpoint` when protocol is set and endpoint lacks a scheme. The system SHALL use `httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy`, shared `http.Transport` on the proxy, and custom `Director` to set path, host, forwarding headers, and optional JWT.\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: No entry points\n41: - **GIVEN** `EntryPoints` is empty\n42: - **WHEN** upstream is determined\n43: - **THEN** the handler responds 404 JSON `{\"error\":\"no entry point found for sandbox\"}`\n44: \n45: ### Requirement: JWT injection for sandbox kinds\n46: For sandbox kinds `Sandbox` and `SandboxClaim`, the system SHALL generate a JWT before proxying and SHALL set `Authorization: Bearer <token>` on the proxied request.\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: Signing failure\n49: - **GIVEN** JWT generation returns an error\n50: - **WHEN** forwarding is attempted\n51: - **THEN** the handler responds 500 with JSON containing `\"code\":\"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\"` and `\"error\":\"failed to sign request\"`\n52: \n53: ### Requirement: Forwarding headers and response header\n54: The system SHALL set `X-Forwarded-Host` from the incoming request host, `X-Forwarded-Proto` to `https` when TLS is present else `http`, and `X-Forwarded-For` by appending client IP to any existing values. The system SHALL set response header `x-agentcube-session-id` to the resolved session id on all proxied responses.\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Path normalization\n57: - **GIVEN** the Gin path param is non-empty and lacks a leading slash\n58: - **WHEN** the director runs\n59: - **THEN** the outbound path is prefixed with `/`\n60: \n61: ### Requirement: Proxy error mapping\n62: The system SHALL map proxy errors containing `connection refused` to 502 `{\"error\":\"sandbox unreachable\"}`, containing `timeout` to 504 `{\"error\":\"sandbox timeout\"}`, and other errors to 502 `{\"error\":\"sandbox unreachable\"}`.\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Downstream connection refused\n65: - **GIVEN** the reverse proxy fails with an error whose message includes `connection refused`\n66: - **WHEN** `ErrorHandler` runs\n67: - **THEN** status is 502 and error text is `sandbox unreachable`\n68: \n69: ### Requirement: Last-activity updates\n70: The system SHALL call `UpdateSessionLastActivity` with `time.Now()` after successfully resolving the sandbox and again after `forwardToSandbox` returns (twice per successful invoke path). Failures SHALL be logged as warnings only.\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: Store update failure does not block proxy\n73: - **GIVEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` returns an error\n74: - **WHEN** handling continues\n75: - **THEN** the proxy still runs if sandbox resolution succeeded\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: Health endpoints\n78: The system SHALL expose `GET /health/live` returning 200 `{\"status\":\"alive\"}`. The system SHALL expose `GET /health/ready` returning 200 `{\"status\":\"ready\"}` when session manager is non-nil, else 503 with `status` and `error` fields.\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Ready depends on session manager\n81: - **GIVEN** `sessionManager` is nil\n82: - **WHEN** `GET /health/ready` is served\n83: - **THEN** status is 503 and body includes `\"error\":\"session manager not available\"`\n84: \n85: ### Requirement: Concurrency limiting\n86: The system SHALL apply a semaphore middleware to `/v1/*` routes with capacity `MaxConcurrentRequests` (default 1000 when config value ≤ 0). When no slot is available, the system SHALL respond 429 JSON `{\"error\":\"server overloaded, please try again later\",\"code\":\"SERVER_OVERLOADED\"}` and abort.\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Default limit when zero in config\n89: - **GIVEN** `NewServer` receives `MaxConcurrentRequests` 0\n90: - **WHEN** the server is constructed\n91: - **THEN** the effective limit is set to 1000 before route registration\n92: \n93: ### Requirement: Invocation route surface\n94: The system SHALL register GET and POST for `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` and for `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path`, with Gin logger, recovery, and concurrency middleware on the `/v1` group only.\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: Kind passed to session lookup\n97: - **GIVEN** agent-runtime invocation\n98: - **WHEN** `handleInvoke` runs\n99: - **THEN** kind argument is `AgentRuntime` (`types.AgentRuntimeKind`)\n100: \n101: ### Requirement: HTTP server behavior\n102: The system SHALL serve with `h2c` and `http2.Server`, `ReadTimeout` 30s, `IdleTimeout` 90s; on context cancel SHALL shutdown within 10s. Optional TLS SHALL require both cert and key paths.\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: TLS misconfiguration\n105: - **GIVEN** `EnableTLS` true and empty cert path\n106: - **WHEN** `Start` runs\n107: - **THEN** it returns error stating cert/key not provided\n108: \n109: ### Requirement: Identity secret bootstrap for JWT\n110: On server creation the system SHALL construct `JWTManager`, call `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret`, and fail server creation if that returns error (except in-cluster skip path returns nil when not in cluster).\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: In-cluster secret creation\n113: - **GIVEN** in-cluster config succeeds and secret does not exist\n114: - **WHEN** `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret` runs\n115: - **THEN** it creates opaque secret `picod-router-identity` in namespace from `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` or `default` with keys `private.pem` and `public.pem`\n\n(End of file - total 115 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Session Routing Specification\n\n## Purpose\nRoute HTTP invocation traffic to sandboxes by session: resolve or create sessions via the workload manager, track activity in the store, reverse-proxy to pod endpoints, and sign outbound requests with JWT when targeting sandboxes.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Session resolution and creation\nThe system SHALL read session id from request header `x-agentcube-session-id`. When the header is empty, the system SHALL POST to the workload manager to create a sandbox. When non-empty, the system SHALL load `SandboxInfo` from the store by session id.\n\n#### Scenario: Missing session triggers workload manager create\n- **GIVEN** `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is set and an invocation request has no `x-agentcube-session-id`\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySession` runs for `AgentRuntimeKind`\n- **THEN** the client POSTs JSON `{\"kind\":\"AgentRuntime\",\"name\":...,\"namespace\":...}` to `{WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/agent-runtime`\n\n#### Scenario: Unknown session returns not found\n- **GIVEN** a non-empty session id not present in store\n- **WHEN** the store returns `ErrNotFound`\n- **THEN** the error maps to `NewSessionNotFoundError(sessionID)` and the HTTP handler responds using API status (typically 404)\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/session-routing/spec.md","time":{"start":1775861795900,"end":1775861795913}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861795933,"sessionID":"ses_286640c0dffe2rD36uP62Wo9IW","part":{"id":"prt_d799c87a0001RVhP2Mh5euKCU8","messageID":"msg_d799c5e62001TZDjDoglNroXtW","sessionID":"ses_286640c0dffe2rD36uP62Wo9IW","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:10","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-009/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-009/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-009 Design: Router HTTP 反向代理核心\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-009  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/router`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** M\n9: \n10: The Router HTTP Reverse Proxy Core serves as the edge gateway for AgentCube, handling all invocation traffic from external clients to sandbox pods. The Router accepts HTTP requests, resolves sessions to sandbox endpoints via the session store, reverse-proxies traffic to the appropriate sandbox pods, and integrates with the Workload Manager for sandbox creation on cache misses. It provides JWT-based request signing for secure sandbox communication.\n11: \n12: ### Key Responsibilities\n13: \n14: 1. **HTTP Gateway**: Exposes RESTful endpoints for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter invocations\n15: 2. **Session Resolution**: Resolves sessions from the store or creates new sandboxes via Workload Manager\n16: 3. **Reverse Proxy**: Proxies HTTP/1.1 and HTTP/2 (h2c) traffic to sandbox pods\n17: 4. **JWT Authentication**: Generates RS256-signed JWT tokens for secure sandbox communication\n18: 5. **Health Monitoring**: Provides liveness and readiness probes for Kubernetes\n19: 6. **Concurrency Control**: Limits concurrent requests to prevent overload\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## Architecture\n24: \n25: ### High-Level Design\n26: \n27: ```\n28: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n29: │                              External Clients                                    │\n30: │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐                             │\n31: │  │   Web UI    │  │   CLI Tool  │  │  Agent SDK  │                             │\n32: │  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘                             │\n33: └─────────┼────────────────┼────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────┘\n34:           │                │                │\n35:           ▼                ▼                ▼\n36: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n37: │                              Router HTTP Server                                  │\n38: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n39: │  │                           HTTP Server Layer                                 │ │\n40: │  │  · h2c support (HTTP/2 without TLS)                                         │ │\n41: │  │  · Optional TLS termination                                                 │ │\n42: │  │  · ReadTimeout: 30s, IdleTimeout: 90s                                       │ │\n43: │  │  · Graceful shutdown with 10s timeout                                       │ │\n44: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n45: │                                    │                                             │\n46: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────▼──────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n47: │  │                           Gin Router Layer                                  │ │\n48: │  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │ │\n49: │  │  │  Health Routes (no middleware)                                      │    │ │\n50: │  │  │  · GET /health/live  → handleHealthLive                             │    │ │\n51: │  │  │  · GET /health/ready → handleHealthReady                            │    │ │\n52: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │ │\n53: │  │                                    │                                         │ │\n54: │  │  ┌─────────────────────────────────▼────────────────────────────────────┐   │ │\n55: │  │  │  V1 Routes (with middleware: Logger, Recovery, ConcurrencyLimit)      │   │ │\n56: │  │  │                                                                       │   │ │\n57: │  │  │  AgentRuntime Routes:                                                 │   │ │\n58: │  │  │  · GET/POST /v1/namespaces/:ns/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path │   │ │\n59: │  │  │                                                                       │   │ │\n60: │  │  │  CodeInterpreter Routes:                                              │   │ │\n61: │  │  │  · GET/POST /v1/namespaces/:ns/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*  │   │ │\n62: │  │  │                                                                       │   │ │\n63: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │ │\n64: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n65: │                                    │                                             │\n66: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────▼──────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n67: │  │                           Handler Layer                                     │ │\n68: │  │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐ │ │\n69: │  │  │ Session Resolution│  │ JWT Generation   │  │ Reverse Proxy            │ │ │\n70: │  │  │ · Header extract │  │ · RS256 signing  │  │ · URL resolution         │ │ │\n71: │  │  │ · Store lookup   │  │ · Key management │  │ · Header forwarding      │ │ │\n72: │  │  │ · WM create      │  │ · Token injection│  │ · Error handling         │ │ │\n73: │  │  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘ │ │\n74: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n75: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n76:           │\n77:           ▼\n78: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n79: │                           External Dependencies                                  │\n80: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────────┐  │\n81: │  │   Session Store  │  │ Workload Manager │  │ Kubernetes API               │  │\n82: │  │   (pkg/store)    │  │   (HTTP Client)  │  │ (JWT Secret, In-Cluster)     │  │\n83: │  │                  │  │                  │  │                              │  │\n84: │  │ · GetSession     │  │ · CreateSandbox  │  │ · Secret CRUD                │  │\n85: │  │ · UpdateActivity │  │ · GetSandboxInfo │  │ · Service Account Token      │  │\n86: │  │ · StoreSandbox   │  │ · Auth Token     │  │ · In-cluster detection       │  │\n87: │  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────────────────┘  │\n88: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n89: ```\n90: \n91: ### Component Interactions\n92: \n93: ```\n94: ┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐\n95: │   Client    │────▶│    Router   │────▶│ SessionManager  │────▶│    Store    │\n96: │   Request   │     │   Server    │     │                 │     │             │\n97: └─────────────┘     └─────────────┘     └─────────────────┘     └─────────────┘\n98:                                               │                         │\n99:                                               ▼                         │\n100:                                         ┌─────────────┐                 │\n101:                                         │   Workload  │                 │\n102:                                         │   Manager   │◄────────────────┘\n103:                                         └─────────────┘   (if not found)\n104:                                               │\n105:                                               ▼\n106:                                         ┌─────────────┐\n107:                                         │  Sandbox    │\n108:                                         │    Pod      │\n109:                                         └─────────────┘\n110: ```\n111: \n112: ---\n113: \n114: ## Data Structures\n115: \n116: ### Configuration\n117: \n118: ```go\n119: // Config holds router configuration parameters.\n120: type Config struct {\n121:     // Port is the HTTP server port (default: \"8080\")\n122:     Port string\n123: \n124:     // Debug enables Gin debug mode (default: false)\n125:     Debug bool\n126: \n127:     // EnableTLS enables TLS termination (default: false)\n128:     EnableTLS bool\n129: \n130:     // TLSCert is the path to TLS certificate file\n131:     TLSCert string\n132: \n133:     // TLSKey is the path to TLS key file\n134:     TLSKey string\n135: \n136:     // MaxConcurrentRequests limits concurrent proxy requests (default: 1000)\n137:     MaxConcurrentRequests int\n138: }\n139: ```\n140: \n141: ### Server State\n142: \n143: ```go\n144: // Server represents the HTTP router server.\n145: type Server struct {\n146:     config         *Config\n147:     engine         *gin.Engine\n148:     httpServer     *http.Server\n149:     sessionManager SessionManager\n150:     storeClient    store.Store\n151:     httpTransport  *http.Transport\n152:     jwtManager     *JWTManager\n153: }\n154: ```\n155: \n156: ### Session Management\n157: \n158: ```go\n159: // SessionManager defines the interface for session resolution.\n160: type SessionManager interface {\n161:     GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace string, name string, kind string) (*SandboxInfo, error)\n162: }\n163: \n164: // manager implements SessionManager.\n165: type manager struct {\n166:     storeClient     store.Store\n167:     workloadMgrAddr string\n168:     httpClient      *http.Client\n169: }\n170: \n171: // SandboxInfo contains information about a resolved sandbox.\n172: type SandboxInfo struct {\n173:     SandboxID   string\n174:     Name        string\n175:     Namespace   string\n176:     SessionID   string\n177:     Kind        string\n178:     PodIP       string\n179:     PodName     string\n180:     EntryPoints []EntryPoint\n181:     Status      string\n182: }\n183: \n184: // EntryPoint defines an access point to the sandbox.\n185: type EntryPoint struct {\n186:     Protocol string // \"http\" or \"https\"\n187:     Endpoint string // host:port\n188:     Path     string // base path\n189: }\n190: \n191: // CreateSandboxRequest is sent to Workload Manager.\n192: type CreateSandboxRequest struct {\n193:     Kind      string `json:\"kind\"`\n194:     Name      string `json:\"name\"`\n195:     Namespace string `json:\"namespace\"`\n196: }\n197: \n198: // CreateSandboxResponse is received from Workload Manager.\n199: type CreateSandboxResponse struct {\n200:     SessionID   string       `json:\"sessionId\"`\n201:     SandboxID   string       `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n202:     Name        string       `json:\"name\"`\n203:     Namespace   string       `json:\"namespace\"`\n204:     EntryPoints []EntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n205:     Status      string       `json:\"status\"`\n206: }\n207: ```\n208: \n209: ### JWT Management\n210: \n211: ```go\n212: // JWTManager handles JWT signing and key management.\n213: type JWTManager struct {\n214:     privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n215:     publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n216:     clientset  kubernetes.Interface\n217: }\n218: \n219: // JWTClaims represents the JWT payload.\n220: type JWTClaims struct {\n221:     jwt.RegisteredClaims\n222:     SessionID string `json:\"session_id,omitempty\"`\n223: }\n224: ```\n225: \n226: ### Error Types\n227: \n228: ```go\n229: // RouterError represents a router-specific error.\n230: type RouterError struct {\n231:     Code    string\n232:     Message string\n233:     Status  int\n234: }\n235: \n236: // Specific error codes\n237: const (\n238:     ErrCodeSessionNotFound       = \"SESSION_NOT_FOUND\"\n239:     ErrCodeSandboxNotFound       = \"SANDBOX_NOT_FOUND\"\n240:     ErrCodeSandboxTemplateNotFound = \"SANDBOX_TEMPLATE_NOT_FOUND\"\n241:     ErrCodeJWTSigningFailed      = \"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\"\n242:     ErrCodeServerOverloaded      = \"SERVER_OVERLOADED\"\n243:     ErrCodeSandboxUnreachable    = \"SANDBOX_UNREACHABLE\"\n244:     ErrCodeSandboxTimeout        = \"SANDBOX_TIMEOUT\"\n245: )\n246: ```\n247: \n248: ---\n249: \n250: ## API Contracts\n251: \n252: ### Health Endpoints\n253: \n254: | Method | Path | Response | Description |\n255: |--------|------|----------|-------------|\n256: | GET | `/health/live` | `{\"status\":\"alive\"}` | Liveness probe |\n257: | GET | `/health/ready` | `{\"status\":\"ready\"}` or `{\"status\":\"not ready\",\"error\":\"...\"}` | Readiness probe |\n258: \n259: ### Invocation Endpoints\n260: \n261: | Method | Path | Headers | Description |\n262: |--------|------|---------|-------------|\n263: | GET | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | `x-agentcube-session-id` | Proxy to AgentRuntime |\n264: | POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | `x-agentcube-session-id` | Proxy to AgentRuntime |\n265: | GET | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | `x-agentcube-session-id` | Proxy to CodeInterpreter |\n266: | POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | `x-agentcube-session-id` | Proxy to CodeInterpreter |\n267: \n268: ### Request Headers\n269: \n270: | Header | Required | Description |\n271: |--------|----------|-------------|\n272: | `x-agentcube-session-id` | No | Session identifier for existing sessions |\n273: | `Authorization` | No | Client authentication (forwarded to sandbox) |\n274: | `Content-Type` | Yes | Request body format |\n275: \n276: ### Response Headers\n277: \n278: | Header | Description |\n279: |--------|-------------|\n280: | `x-agentcube-session-id` | Resolved session ID |\n281: | `X-Forwarded-Host` | Original request host |\n282: | `X-Forwarded-Proto` | Original request protocol |\n283: | `X-Forwarded-For` | Client IP chain |\n284: \n285: ---\n286: \n287: ## Error Handling\n288: \n289: ### HTTP Status Code Mapping\n290: \n291: | Error Condition | HTTP Status | Error Message | Error Code |\n292: |-----------------|-------------|---------------|------------|\n293: | Session not found | 404 | session not found | SESSION_NOT_FOUND |\n294: | Sandbox template not found | 404 | sandbox template not found | SANDBOX_TEMPLATE_NOT_FOUND |\n295: | No entry points | 404 | no entry point found for sandbox | - |\n296: | JWT signing failure | 500 | failed to sign request | JWT_SIGNING_FAILED |\n297: | Server overloaded | 429 | server overloaded, please try again later | SERVER_OVERLOADED |\n298: | Connection refused | 502 | sandbox unreachable | - |\n299: | Timeout | 504 | sandbox timeout | - |\n300: | Other proxy errors | 502 | sandbox unreachable | - |\n301: \n302: ### Error Response Format\n303: \n304: ```json\n305: {\n306:   \"error\": \"human-readable message\",\n307:   \"code\": \"ERROR_CODE\"\n308: }\n309: ```\n310: \n311: ### Error Handling Strategy\n312: \n313: 1. **Session Resolution Errors**: Map store errors to appropriate HTTP status codes\n314: 2. **Workload Manager Errors**: Propagate HTTP status codes, map 404 to template not found\n315: 3. **Proxy Errors**: Intercept transport errors and map to 502/504 with user-friendly messages\n316: 4. **JWT Errors**: Return 500 for signing failures, log detailed error\n317: 5. **Store Update Errors**: Log warnings, do not block proxy flow\n318: \n319: ---\n320: \n321: ## Algorithms\n322: \n323: ### Session Resolution Algorithm\n324: \n325: ```\n326: function GetSandboxBySession(sessionID, namespace, name, kind):\n327:     if sessionID is empty:\n328:         return createNewSandbox(namespace, name, kind)\n329:     \n330:     sandboxInfo, err := storeClient.GetSession(sessionID)\n331:     if err == ErrNotFound:\n332:         return nil, NewSessionNotFoundError(sessionID)\n333:     if err != nil:\n334:         return nil, err\n335:     \n336:     return sandboxInfo, nil\n337: \n338: function createNewSandbox(namespace, name, kind):\n339:     req := CreateSandboxRequest{Kind: kind, Name: name, Namespace: namespace}\n340:     resp, err := postToWorkloadManager(req)\n341:     if err != nil:\n342:         return nil, err\n343:     \n344:     if resp.SessionID == \"\":\n345:         return nil, NewValidationError(\"sessionId is empty\")\n346:     \n347:     sandboxInfo := SandboxInfo{\n348:         SandboxID:   resp.SandboxID,\n349:         Name:        resp.Name,\n350:         SessionID:   resp.SessionID,\n351:         EntryPoints: resp.EntryPoints,\n352:     }\n353:     \n354:     // Store in cache\n355:     storeClient.StoreSession(sandboxInfo.SessionID, sandboxInfo)\n356:     \n357:     return sandboxInfo, nil\n358: ```\n359: \n360: ### Upstream URL Resolution\n361: \n362: ```\n363: function resolveUpstreamURL(sandboxInfo, invocationPath):\n364:     if len(sandboxInfo.EntryPoints) == 0:\n365:         return nil, NewNoEntryPointError()\n366:     \n367:     // Find matching entry point by path prefix\n368:     for _, ep := range sandboxInfo.EntryPoints:\n369:         if strings.HasPrefix(invocationPath, ep.Path):\n370:             return buildURL(ep, invocationPath), nil\n371:     }\n372:     \n373:     // Fall back to first entry point\n374:     return buildURL(sandboxInfo.EntryPoints[0], invocationPath), nil\n375: \n376: function buildURL(entryPoint, path):\n377:     url := entryPoint.Endpoint\n378:     if entryPoint.Protocol != \"\" && !strings.Contains(url, \"://\"):\n379:         url = entryPoint.Protocol + \"://\" + url\n380:     }\n381:     \n382:     // Normalize path\n383:     if path != \"\" && !strings.HasPrefix(path, \"/\"):\n384:         path = \"/\" + path\n385:     }\n386:     \n387:     return url + path\n388: ```\n389: \n390: ### JWT Generation\n391: \n392: ```\n393: function GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}):\n394:     now := time.Now()\n395:     baseClaims := JWTClaims{\n396:         RegisteredClaims: jwt.RegisteredClaims{\n397:             ExpiresAt: jwt.NewNumericDate(now.Add(jwtExpiration)),\n398:             IssuedAt:  jwt.NewNumericDate(now),\n399:             Issuer:    \"agentcube-router\",\n400:         },\n401:     }\n402:     \n403:     // Merge custom claims\n404:     for k, v := range claims:\n405:         if k == \"session_id\":\n406:             baseClaims.SessionID = v.(string)\n407:         }\n408:     }\n409:     \n410:     token := jwt.NewWithClaims(jwt.SigningMethodRS256, baseClaims)\n411:     return token.SignedString(privateKey)\n412: ```\n413: \n414: ### Concurrency Limiting\n415: \n416: ```\n417: function concurrencyLimitMiddleware(limit int):\n418:     semaphore := make(chan struct{}, limit)\n419:     \n420:     return func(c *gin.Context):\n421:         select:\n422:             case semaphore <- struct{}{}:\n423:                 defer func() { <-semaphore }()\n424:                 c.Next()\n425:             default:\n426:                 c.AbortWithStatusJSON(429, {\n427:                     \"error\": \"server overloaded, please try again later\",\n428:                     \"code\": \"SERVER_OVERLOADED\"\n429:                 })\n430:         }\n431:     }\n432: ```\n433: \n434: ---\n435: \n436: ## Testing Strategy\n437: \n438: ### Unit Tests\n439: \n440: | Component | Test Cases | Mock Dependencies |\n441: |-----------|------------|-------------------|\n442: | Server | Configuration validation, route registration | - |\n443: | SessionManager | Session resolution, WM integration, error handling | Store, HTTP Client |\n444: | JWTManager | Token generation, key persistence, signing | K8s Client |\n445: | Proxy | URL resolution, header forwarding, error mapping | HTTP Transport |\n446: | Middleware | Concurrency limiting, request ID | - |\n447: \n448: ### Integration Tests\n449: \n450: | Scenario | Description |\n451: |----------|-------------|\n452: | Full request flow | Client → Router → Sandbox with mocked store |\n453: | Session creation | Missing session ID triggers WM create |\n454: | Session reuse | Existing session loaded from store |\n455: | JWT injection | Token generated and attached to proxied request |\n456: | Health probes | Live and ready endpoints respond correctly |\n457: | Concurrency limit | Requests rejected when limit exceeded |\n458: | Error handling | Various error conditions return correct status codes |\n459: \n460: ### Test Data\n461: \n462: ```go\n463: // Example SandboxInfo for tests\n464: var testSandboxInfo = &SandboxInfo{\n465:     SandboxID:   \"sb-12345\",\n466:     Name:        \"test-agent\",\n467:     Namespace:   \"default\",\n468:     SessionID:   \"sess-abc-123\",\n469:     Kind:        \"AgentRuntime\",\n470:     PodIP:       \"10.0.0.1\",\n471:     PodName:     \"test-agent-abc123\",\n472:     EntryPoints: []EntryPoint{\n473:         {Protocol: \"http\", Endpoint: \"10.0.0.1:8080\", Path: \"/\"},\n474:     },\n475:     Status: \"Running\",\n476: }\n477: ```\n478: \n479: ---\n480: \n481: ## Configuration\n482: \n483: ### Environment Variables\n484: \n485: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n486: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n487: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Yes | - | Workload Manager base URL |\n488: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | No | \"default\" | Namespace for JWT secret |\n489: \n490: ### CLI Flags\n491: \n492: | Flag | Default | Description |\n493: |------|---------|-------------|\n494: | `-port` | \"8080\" | HTTP server port |\n495: | `-enable-tls` | false | Enable TLS termination |\n496: | `-tls-cert` | \"\" | TLS certificate file path |\n497: | `-tls-key` | \"\" | TLS key file path |\n498: | `-debug` | false | Enable Gin debug mode |\n499: | `-max-concurrent-requests` | 1000 | Max concurrent requests |\n500: \n501: ### Default Values\n502: \n503: ```go\n504: const (\n505:     defaultPort                  = \"8080\"\n506:     defaultMaxConcurrentRequests = 1000\n507:     defaultReadTimeout           = 30 * time.Second\n508:     defaultIdleTimeout           = 90 * time.Second\n509:     defaultShutdownTimeout       = 10 * time.Second\n510:     \n511:     defaultJWTExpiration = 5 * time.Minute\n512:     defaultRSAKeySize    = 2048\n513: )\n514: ```\n515: \n516: ---\n517: \n518: ## Dependencies\n519: \n520: ### Direct Dependencies\n521: \n522: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n523: |---------|---------|---------|\n524: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.9+ | HTTP web framework |\n525: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.x | JWT signing and validation |\n526: | `golang.org/x/net/http2` | Latest | HTTP/2 support |\n527: | `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.32.0 | Kubernetes API client |\n528: | `k8s.io/api` | v0.32.0 | Kubernetes API types |\n529: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | v0.32.0 | Kubernetes API machinery |\n530: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.x | Structured logging |\n531: \n532: ### Internal Dependencies\n533: \n534: | Package | Purpose |\n535: |---------|---------|\n536: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Session store interface |\n537: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | Shared types |\n538: \n539: ---\n540: \n541: ## File Structure\n542: \n543: ```\n544: pkg/router/\n545: ├── server.go           # HTTP server setup, Gin engine, route registration\n546: ├── proxy.go            # Reverse proxy implementation with httputil\n547: ├── session_manager.go  # Session resolution and sandbox lookup\n548: ├── jwt.go              # JWT generation, signing, key management\n549: ├── config.go           # Configuration types and constants\n550: ├── handlers.go         # HTTP handler functions\n551: ├── middleware.go       # Concurrency limiting and custom middleware\n552: ├── health.go           # Health check handlers\n553: ├── errors.go           # Error types and codes\n554: └── doc.go              # Package documentation\n555: \n556: cmd/router/\n557: └── main.go             # Entry point, CLI flags, server lifecycle\n558: ```\n559: \n560: ---\n561: \n562: ## Constants Reference\n563: \n564: | Name | Value | Description |\n565: |------|-------|-------------|\n566: | `LastActivityAnnotationKey` | `\"agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity\"` | Annotation key for last activity |\n567: | `rsaKeySize` | `2048` | RSA key size for JWT signing |\n568: | `jwtExpiration` | `5 * time.Minute` | JWT token expiration |\n569: | `IdentitySecretName` | `\"picod-router-identity\"` | Kubernetes secret name for JWT keys |\n570: | `PrivateKeyDataKey` | `\"private.pem\"` | Secret data key for private key |\n571: | `PublicKeyDataKey` | `\"public.pem\"` | Secret data key for public key |\n572: \n573: ---\n574: \n575: ## Implementation Notes\n576: \n577: 1. **HTTP/2 Support**: The Router uses h2c (HTTP/2 without TLS) for internal communication, enabling efficient multiplexing of requests to sandbox pods.\n578: \n579: 2. **JWT Key Persistence**: RSA keys are stored in Kubernetes secrets to ensure pod restart resilience. When not running in-cluster, ephemeral keys are generated.\n580: \n581: 3. **Session Creation Delegation**: Creating new sandboxes is delegated to the Workload Manager to avoid duplicating orchestration logic.\n582: \n583: 4. **Connection Pooling**: A shared `http.Transport` is used for connection pooling and reuse when proxying to sandboxes.\n584: \n585: 5. **WebSocket Support**: WebSocket upgrade is supported via reverse proxy passthrough.\n586: \n587: 6. **Best-Effort Activity Tracking**: Last-activity updates are logged as warnings on failure but do not block the proxy flow.\n588: \n589: 7. **Path Normalization**: The Director ensures all outbound paths start with `/` for consistent routing.\n590: \n591: ---\n592: \n593: ## Related Documents\n594: \n595: - [Delta Specification](delta-spec.md) - Detailed requirements and scenarios\n596: - [Client-Go Library](../../deployment/client-go.md) - Kubernetes client usage\n597: - [Session Routing Design](../../session-routing/design.md) - High-level routing design\n\n(End of file - total 597 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-009 Design: Router HTTP 反向代理核心\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-009  \n**Module:** `pkg/router`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\nThe Router HTTP Reverse Proxy Core serves as the edge gateway for AgentCube, handling all invocation traffic from external clients to sandbox pods. The Router accepts HTTP requests, resolves sessions to sandbox endpoints via the session store, reverse-proxies traffic to the appropriate sandbox pods, and integrates with the Workload Manager for sandbox creation on cache misses. It provides JWT-based request signing for secure sandbox communication.\n\n### Key Responsibilities\n\n1. **HTTP Gateway**: Exposes RESTful endpoints for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter invocations\n2. **Session Resolution**: Resolves sessions from the store or creates new sandboxes via Workload Manager\n3. **Reverse Proxy**: Proxies HTTP/1.1 and HTTP/2 (h2c) traffic to sandbox pods\n4. **JWT Authentication**: Generates RS256-signed JWT tokens for secure sandbox communication\n5. **Health Monitoring**: Provides liveness and readiness probes for Kubernetes\n6. **Concurrency Control**: Limits concurrent requests to prevent overload\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-009/design.md","time":{"start":1775861795901,"end":1775861795928}}}}
