{"type":"text","timestamp":1775861802601,"sessionID":"ses_286640c0dffe2rD36uP62Wo9IW","part":{"id":"prt_d799ca49e0014G2zdaSfIGhDrI","messageID":"msg_d799c8c99001dXI9Q1BUGdorDb","sessionID":"ses_286640c0dffe2rD36uP62Wo9IW","type":"text","text":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the project. Let me write the proposal.md for AR-011:","time":{"start":1775861802598,"end":1775861802598}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775861858969,"sessionID":"ses_286640c0dffe2rD36uP62Wo9IW","part":{"id":"prt_d799d5b7f001PfvJFsy6NHpDmA","messageID":"msg_d799c8c99001dXI9Q1BUGdorDb","sessionID":"ses_286640c0dffe2rD36uP62Wo9IW","type":"text","text":" maximum","time":{"start":1775861858966,"end":1775861858966}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861859037,"sessionID":"ses_286640c0dffe2rD36uP62Wo9IW","part":{"id":"prt_d799ca668001ZFls3kjQcnLT3D","messageID":"msg_d799c8c99001dXI9Q1BUGdorDb","sessionID":"ses_286640c0dffe2rD36uP62Wo9IW","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:11","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","content":"# AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 (Router JWT Authentication and Issuance)\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement JWT (JSON Web Token) authentication and issuance functionality in `pkg/router` to provide secure, stateless authentication for requests between the Router and sandbox pods. The JWT Manager serves as the security foundation for the AgentCube routing layer, handling RSA key generation, token signing, and key persistence in Kubernetes secrets.\n\nThe JWT Manager provides three primary responsibilities:\n1. **Token Generation**: Creates RS256-signed JWT tokens with configurable claims for session identification\n2. **Key Management**: Generates and persists RSA 2048-bit key pairs, with automatic storage in Kubernetes secrets for cluster resilience\n3. **Authentication**: Signs proxied requests to sandbox pods, enabling the sandbox to verify request authenticity\n\nThis AR builds upon the HTTP reverse proxy core (AR-009) and session management (AR-010) to add the security layer required for trusted communication between Router and sandboxes.\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router` |\n| **Core functionality** | JWT token generation (RS256), RSA key pair management, Kubernetes secret persistence |\n| **Integration with** | Kubernetes API (Secret storage), Router HTTP handlers (token injection) |\n| **Token claims** | Standard claims (exp, iat, iss) + custom claims (session_id) |\n| **Key storage** | Kubernetes Secret `picod-router-identity` with `private.pem` and `public.pem` |\n| **Configuration** | Namespace via `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env var (default: `default`) |\n| **Algorithm** | RS256 (RSA with SHA-256) |\n\n### Out of scope\n\n- JWT token validation/verification (handled by sandbox pods consuming the tokens)\n- OAuth2/OIDC integration (bearer token authentication is AR-012)\n- Certificate-based authentication (mTLS handled separately)\n- Token refresh mechanism (short-lived 5-minute tokens, sessions manage lifecycle)\n- JWT revocation list (rely on short expiration and session termination)\n- Key rotation automation (initial implementation uses fixed keys per deployment)\n\n---\n\n## Design\n\n### File layout\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pkg/router/jwt.go` | **EXISTING/ENHANCED** — JWTManager implementation, key generation, token signing |\n\n### Type definitions\n\n**`JWTManager`** — JWT management struct:\n\n```go\n// JWTManager handles JWT key generation and token signing.\ntype JWTManager struct {\n    privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n    publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n    clientset  kubernetes.Interface\n}\n```\n\n**Key methods:**\n\n```go\n// NewJWTManager creates a new JWTManager with a generated RSA key pair.\nfunc NewJWTManager() (*JWTManager, error)\n\n// GenerateToken creates a JWT with the given claims.\nfunc (m *JWTManager) GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)\n\n// GetPublicKeyPEM returns the public key in PEM format.\nfunc (m *JWTManager) GetPublicKeyPEM() ([]byte, error)\n\n// GetPrivateKeyPEM returns the private key in PEM format.\nfunc (m *JWTManager) GetPrivateKeyPEM() ([]byte, error)\n\n// TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret attempts to store keys in K8s secret or load existing.\nfunc (m *JWTManager) TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret() error\n```\n\n### Token Generation Flow\n\n```\nHTTP Request Received\n         │\n         ▼\nSession Resolved (AR-010)\n         │\n         ▼\nJWTManager.GenerateToken\n         │\n    ┌────┴────┐\n    ▼         ▼\nBase Claims   Custom Claims\n- exp         - session_id\n- iat         (from SessionInfo)\n- iss         \n    │         │\n    └────┬────┘\n         ▼\nSign with RS256\n(private key)\n         │\n         ▼\nAuthorization: Bearer <token>\n(set on proxied request)\n```\n\n### Key Persistence Flow\n\n```\nServer Startup\n         │\n         ▼\nNewJWTManager()\n(generate new RSA key pair)\n         │\n         ▼\nTryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret\n         │\n    ┌────┴─────────────────┐\n    │                      │\nIn-cluster?            Not in-cluster\n    │                      │\n    ▼                      ▼\nCreate Secret          Log warning\n(or load existing)     Use ephemeral keys\n         │\n         ▼\nSecret 'picod-router-identity'\n├── private.pem (RSA PRIVATE KEY)\n└── public.pem  (PUBLIC KEY)\n```\n\n### Token Claims Structure\n\n```go\n// Base claims (always included)\n{\n    \"exp\": <unix_timestamp>,      // Expiration: now + 5 minutes\n    \"iat\": <unix_timestamp>,      // Issued at: now\n    \"iss\": \"agentcube-router\"     // Issuer\n}\n\n// With custom claims\n{\n    \"exp\": 1710000000,\n    \"iat\": 1709999700,\n    \"iss\": \"agentcube-router\",\n    \"session_id\": \"sess-abc-123\"  // From SessionInfo.SessionID\n}\n```\n\n### Constants\n\n| Name | Value | Description |\n|------|-------|-------------|\n| `rsaKeySize` | `2048` | RSA key size in bits |\n| `jwtExpiration` | `5 * time.Minute` | Token validity duration |\n| `identitySecretName` | `\"picod-router-identity\"` | Kubernetes Secret name |\n| `privateKeyDataKey` | `\"private.pem\"` | Secret data key for private key |\n| `publicKeyDataKey` | `\"public.pem\"` | Secret data key for public key |\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | `\"default\"` | Namespace for JWT identity secret |\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Files created/modified\n\n| File | Lines (est.) | Type |\n|------|-------------|------|\n| `pkg/router/jwt.go` | ~220 | Enhanced/Complete |\n\n### Downstream consumers\n\n| Consumer | Dependency |\n|----------|-----------|\n| Router (AR-009) | Uses JWTManager to sign proxied requests |\n| Session Manager (AR-010) | Provides session_id for token claims |\n| Sandbox Pods | Validate JWT tokens using public key |\n| Kubernetes API | Secret storage for key persistence |\n\n### Breaking change risk\n\n- **None for existing APIs**: JWT is additive security enhancement\n- **Key format**: Standard PKCS1/PKIX PEM format, widely compatible\n- **Secret naming**: Uses `picod-router-identity` which doesn't conflict with existing secrets\n- **Algorithm**: RS256 is standard JWT algorithm, well-supported\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### 1. Use HMAC (HS256) instead of RSA (RS256)\n\n**Approach**: Use shared secret key for both signing and verification.\n\n**Rejected because**: RSA allows public key distribution to sandboxes without exposing the private signing key. With HMAC, any sandbox that can verify tokens would need the secret key, creating a security risk if compromised.\n\n### 2. Use Kubernetes Service Account tokens instead of custom JWT\n\n**Approach**: Use `TokenRequest` API to generate projected service account tokens for each request.\n\n**Rejected because**: Service account tokens have different semantics (identity of the Router pod vs. identity of the session). They also have different expiration patterns and aren't suitable for session-scoped claims.\n\n### 3. Use external key management service (KMS/Vault)\n\n**Approach**: Integrate with HashiCorp Vault or cloud KMS for key storage.\n\n**Rejected because**: Adds external dependency and complexity. For the initial implementation, Kubernetes Secret storage provides sufficient security with lower operational overhead. Can be migrated to external KMS later if required.\n\n### 4. Generate new keys on each pod restart\n\n**Approach**: Always generate ephemeral keys, don't persist to secrets.\n\n**Rejected because**: Would invalidate all active sessions on Router restart. Key persistence ensures session continuity across Router restarts and rolling updates.\n\n### 5. Use Ed25519 instead of RSA\n\n**Approach**: Use Ed25519 signatures for smaller key sizes and faster operations.\n\n**Rejected because**: While Ed25519 is preferred for new designs, RSA-2048 is more widely supported by JWT libraries in various languages. RSA was chosen for maximum compatibility with sandbox implementations.\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.x | JWT token signing |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.34.1 | Kubernetes Secret CRUD |\n| `k8s.io/api` | v0.34.1 | Secret API types |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | v0.34.1 | API machinery |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.x | Structured logging |\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\n# Unit tests\nmake test PKG=./pkg/router/...\n\n# Integration tests\ngo test -v ./pkg/router/... -run \"TestJWTManager\"\ngo test -v ./pkg/router/... -run \"TestGenerateToken\"\ngo test -v ./pkg/router/... -run \"TestKeyPersistence\"\n\n# Build verification\ngo build ./pkg/router/...\n\n# Verify JWT token format\ngo test -v ./pkg/router/... -run \"TestTokenClaims\"\n\n# Verify race conditions\ngo test -race ./pkg/router/...\n```\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [Session Routing Design](session-routing/design.md) — Router design details\n- [Session Routing Specification](session-routing/spec.md) — Functional requirements\n- [AR-009](changes/AR-009/design.md) — Router HTTP Reverse Proxy Core\n- [AR-010](changes/AR-010/design.md) — Router Session Management\n- [JWT Specification](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7519) — RFC 7519\n- [JWS Specification](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7515) — RFC 7515 (RS256)\n\n---\n\n*AR-011 — Module: pkg/router — Language: Go — Size: M*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-c