{"type":"text","timestamp":1775861881613,"sessionID":"ses_286640c0dffe2rD36uP62Wo9IW","part":{"id":"prt_d799db8b1001cvC7tfWyDBU1Ys","messageID":"msg_d799d830900172zPVSyHzisltN","sessionID":"ses_286640c0dffe2rD36uP62Wo9IW","type":"text","text":"I have written the `proposal.md` for AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发. The proposal includes:\n\n**Key Sections:**\n\n1. **Purpose** — Explains the JWT Manager's role in providing secure authentication between Router and sandbox pods via RS256-signed tokens\n\n2. **Scope** — \n   - In scope: JWT generation, RSA key management, K8s secret persistence\n   - Out of scope: Token validation (handled by sandboxes), OAuth2/OIDC, token refresh, key rotation\n\n3. **Design** — \n   - File layout (enhanced `jwt.go`)\n   - Type definitions for `JWTManager`\n   - Token generation and key persistence flows\n   - Token claims structure with base claims (exp, iat, iss) + session_id\n   - Constants and environment variables\n\n4. **Impact Analysis** —\n   - Files modified: `pkg/router/jwt.go` (~220 lines)\n   - Downstream consumers: Router, Session Manager, Sandbox Pods, K8s API\n   - Breaking change risk: None (additive security enhancement)\n\n5. **Alternatives Considered** —\n   - HMAC vs RSA (rejected: RS256 allows key distribution without exposing private key)\n   - K8s Service Account tokens (rejected: different semantics)\n   - External KMS/Vault (rejected: added complexity)\n   - Ephemeral keys (rejected: would invalidate sessions on restart)\n   - Ed25519 vs RSA (rejected: RSA has wider library support)\n\n6. **Dependencies** — `golang-jwt/jwt/v5`, `k8s.io/client-go`, `k8s.io/api`, `k8s.io/apimachinery`, `k8s.io/klog/v2`\n\n7. **Verification** — Unit tests, integration tests, build verification, race detection\n\n8. **References** — Related ARs (009, 010), session-routing design/spec, RFC 7519/7515","time":{"start":1775861881609,"end":1775861881609}}}
